gw.api.validation

Class ValidationExecutionResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.validation.ValidationExecutionResult

  • public class ValidationExecutionResult
extends java.lang.Object
    Packages the results of executing Validation on an entity. The EntityKey indicates the bean upon which validation was run, and the ValidationLevel of this execution of validation.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      Key EntityKey
      Key of the root entity upon which Validation was executed.
      java.lang.String[] ErrorMessages
      Returns all Reason messages (both Errors and Warnings) in the Result that are relevant to the ValidationLevel of this execution.
      ValidationIssue[] Issues
      Returns all ValidationIssues (both Errors and Warnings) in the Result that are relevant to the ValidationLevel of this execution.
      ValidationLevel Level
      ValidationLevel of the execution. For normal entity validation, this is the current ValidationLevel of the bean before execution. It is null for special validation executions, such as "Claim Closed Validation rules", in which case all ValidationIssues are reported. Note this property does not affect the ValidationIssues collected during validation, but is used to only return issues whose ValidationLevel has a higher Priority than the ValidationLevel of the execution.
      IValidationResult Result
      The results of executing Validation.
